  "genie_instructions": "ALWAYS prefer metric views with MEASURE() syntax for aggregation questions. The health_monthly view (source: rolling_stock) has dimensions: reading_date, asset_type, fleet. Measures: avg_health_score, avg_vibration, avg_bearing_temp, asset_count, low_health_count. The maintenance_cost_monthly view (source: sensor_readings) has dimensions: event_date, asset_type, event_type, failure_component. Measures: total_parts_cost, total_labor_cost, total_downtime_hours, event_count, emergency_count. Use GROUP BY ALL with MEASURE() queries. Only query base tables directly when the question requires columns not available as metric view dimensions (e.g. asset_id, asset_name).",
